  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Why 1-on-1 Tutoring Works Better Than Group Classes</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Group classes share attention across multiple students, which means you spend most of your time listening rather than speaking. In 1-on-1 tutoring, every minute belongs to you. Your tutor identifies your specific weak spots and focuses entirely on your goals.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Personalized feedback is the key advantage. A tutor who works with you exclusively notices the exact pronunciation patterns, grammar habits, and vocabulary gaps that hold you back. Group classes cannot provide that level of individual attention.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Research consistently shows that learners progress faster with 1-on-1 instruction. The combination of tailored curriculum, immediate correction, and dedicated speaking time creates results that group formats simply cannot match.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">What to Look for in 1-on-1 Tutoring</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Finding the right tutoring platform requires evaluating these five factors:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-6">
    <li><strong>Tutor quality</strong> - Are tutors certified or community-based? Do they specialize in your target goals? Look for verified credentials and positive reviews specifically mentioning your learning objectives.</li>
    <li><strong>Scheduling flexibility</strong> - Can you book lessons that fit your life? Platforms with 24-hour availability, instant booking, and rescheduling options reduce friction and keep practice consistent.</li>
    <li><strong>Lesson structure</strong> - Do lessons follow a curriculum or adapt to your needs? Some learners prefer structured lesson plans while others need flexible conversation practice.</li>
    <li><strong>Value assessment</strong> - Compare the actual cost per speaking minute. A $40/hour lesson with 40 minutes of speaking practice beats a $20/hour lesson with only 15 minutes of active conversation.</li>
    <li><strong>Progress tracking</strong> - Can you measure improvement over time? Platforms that track completed lessons, skill levels, and learning milestones help you stay accountable.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">The 8 Best 1-on-1 English Tutoring Platforms</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3 text-blue-700">1. See Guru</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed"><strong>Best for:</strong> Best overall value with quality Asian tutors</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">See Guru connects learners with tutors from the Philippines and other Asian countries where English is widely spoken as a second language. The platform offers professional lesson materials, progress tracking, and a mobile app for lesson scheduling.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">Tutors range from community tutors offering conversation practice at budget prices to certified teachers with specialized experience in business English, exam preparation, and conversational fluency. Lesson replays let you review material between sessions, which maximizes learning value.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>What makes it stand out:</strong> The combination of low prices and professional infrastructure is rare in the tutoring space. Many tutors have years of experience teaching international students.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4"><strong>Price:</strong> From $5/hour. First lesson at reduced rate.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4"><a href="/reviews/see-guru/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Read our full See Guru review</a></p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3 text-blue-700">2. iTalki</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed"><strong>Best for:</strong> The largest network of tutors for every goal</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">iTalki hosts the largest marketplace of English tutors available anywhere. You can filter by native language, teaching specialization, availability, and price to find tutors who match your exact requirements. The platform covers every time zone and learning goal.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">Community tutors offer conversation practice at budget prices while professional teachers provide structured curriculum for specific goals. The iTalki Notebook adds free vocabulary and writing practice between lessons.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>What makes it stand out:</strong> The sheer size of the marketplace means you can find tutors specializing in niche topics like medical English, legal terminology, or academic writing.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4"><strong>Price:</strong> Community tutors from $5/hour. Professional teachers from $15/hour.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4"><a href="/reviews/italki/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Read our full iTalki review</a></p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3 text-blue-700">3. Preply</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed"><strong>Best for:</strong> Structured learning paths with vetted tutors</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">Preply takes a more curated approach to tutoring. The platform screens tutors more carefully than pure marketplace models, requiring teaching credentials or demonstrated experience before higher-rate listings are approved.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">Preply Campus adds supplementary courses for vocabulary, grammar, and writing practice between tutoring sessions. This structured approach ensures you cover all language skills systematically rather than drifting through random conversations.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>What makes it stand out:</strong> The combination of 1-on-1 tutoring and self-study materials creates a more comprehensive learning experience than pure conversation platforms.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4"><strong>Price:</strong> From $10/hour. Average lesson cost is $25-$35/hour.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4"><a href="/reviews/preply/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Read our full Preply review</a></p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3 text-blue-700">4. Cambly</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed"><strong>Best for:</strong> Instant access to native speakers without booking</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">Cambly flips the traditional booking model. Instead of scheduling lessons in advance, you log in and connect with an available native speaker immediately. This on-demand approach suits learners who want spontaneous practice without planning ahead.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">Tutors come from the US, UK, Australia, and other native English-speaking countries. The Cambly Kids platform offers child-safe sessions with vetted tutors for families.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>What makes it stand out:</strong> The subscription model removes per-lesson anxiety. Practice as much as you want within your subscription period without calculating cost per session.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4"><strong>Price:</strong> Subscription from $14.99/week for limited access. Family plans available.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4"><a href="/reviews/cambly/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Read our full Cambly review</a></p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3 text-blue-700">5. Verbling</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed"><strong>Best for:</strong> European tutors with flexible scheduling options</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">Verbling connects learners with tutors from across Europe, including many UK-based teachers with British English expertise. The platform offers flexible session lengths from 15-minute micro-sessions to 60-minute deep-dive lessons.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">The scheduling system guarantees tutor availability within 24 hours, which removes the frustration of booking far in advance. Video sessions include recording options so you can review lessons later.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>What makes it stand out:</strong> British English specialization sets Verbling apart for learners who specifically want UK pronunciation, vocabulary, and cultural context.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4"><strong>Price:</strong> Tutors from $15/hour. Average prices are $25-$40/hour.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3 text-blue-700">6. Lingoda</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed"><strong>Best for:</strong> Structured group and private classes with certified teachers</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">Lingoda offers both group classes and 1-on-1 private sessions with certified English teachers. The curriculum follows CEFR levels, and class sizes remain small to ensure speaking time for every student.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">The platform covers exam preparation for Cambridge, TOEFL, and IELTS alongside general English courses. Certificates are issued upon completing each level, which provides documented proof of progress.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>What makes it stand out:</strong> The combination of group social learning and private focused instruction creates a balanced approach that works well for learners who want both peer interaction and individual attention.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4"><strong>Price:</strong> Private lessons from $25/session. Group classes from $12/session.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3 text-blue-700">7. iTalki Language Exchange</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed"><strong>Best for:</strong> Free practice with language exchange partners</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">iTalki includes a free language exchange community where learners help each other practice. You find partners who speak your target language and want to learn your native language, creating mutual benefit without any cost.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">The exchange format works best when both partners come prepared with specific topics and goals. Many learners use free exchange to supplement paid tutoring, maximizing speaking time within budget.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>What makes it stand out:</strong> Free access removes financial barriers for consistent speaking practice. The community matching system helps find compatible exchange partners.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4"><strong>Price:</strong> Free</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3 text-blue-700">8. HelloTalk</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed"><strong>Best for:</strong> Free text and voice practice with global language partners</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">HelloTalk connects you with native English speakers who want to learn your language. The app provides free text, voice, and video chat alongside built-in translation and correction tools.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">The Moments feature lets you practice writing English by posting updates that native speakers correct. This community-driven approach builds reading and writing skills alongside conversational practice.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>What makes it stand out:</strong> The correction tools help you understand errors in real time. The social network format makes practice feel less like studying and more like connecting with people worldwide.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4"><strong>Price:</strong> Free with optional VIP subscription from $9.99/month.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">How to Choose the Right 1-on-1 Platform</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">The best platform depends on your specific situation. Consider these factors when making your decision:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-6">
    <li><strong>Budget:</strong> If you need affordable practice, See Guru and iTalki community tutors offer the best value at $5-$10/hour. If you can invest more, Preply and Lingoda provide more structured curriculum.</li>
    <li><strong>Goal type:</strong> For conversation fluency, Cambly and See Guru excel. For exam preparation, Preply and Lingoda offer dedicated curriculum. For business English, look at Verbling and Preply business tutors.</li>
    <li><strong>Availability:</strong> If you need flexible, spontaneous practice, Cambly wins. If you prefer scheduling ahead with a consistent tutor, iTalki and See Guru offer more control over scheduling.</li>
    <li><strong>English variety:</strong> For British English, Verbling specializes in UK tutors. For American English, Cambly and iTalki offer mostly American and international tutors.</li>
  </ul>

